The paper deals with image segmentation, specifically for sky/cloud images captured by ground-based cameras. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also mentions the use of partial least squares (PLS) regression, which is a statistical learning method, indicating a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the release of a large database of annotated images, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) categories.
